headline: Graham Media Group Appoints Michael Storm as Vice President & General Counsel
summary: Graham Media Group, a prominent television broadcasting company, today announced the appointment of Michael Storm as Vice President & General Counsel. Storm brings extensive experience in media law, talent and entertainment contracts, and labor relations from his distinguished career at The Walt Disney Company.

headline: Alaska Air resumes operations, Disney-YouTube TV deadline nears
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton tracks several of the day's top trending stock tickers, including Coinbase Global (COIN) getting an upgrade by JPMorgan analysts, Alaska Air Group (ALK) stock falling in after-hours trading as the airline resumes operations after grounding planes due to an outage, and the deadline for Disney (DIS) and YouTube TV (GOOG, GOOGL) to reach a distribution deal. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: Disney Just Lost 7 Million Subscribers. Does That Even Matter for DIS Stock?
summary: Disney lost 7 million subscribers related to its decision to suspend Jimmy Kimmel. The churn for Disney+ and Hulu also increased in September. However, data shows that Disney is still adding new subscribers at a healthy rate.
